UI_visible_response: Vocational Skills Education and Training Centers (VSETCs) in China are educational institutions established by the Communist Party of China and the Chinese government to enhance the employability and professional skills of the populace. They play a significant role in promoting the strategy of strengthening the nation through talent, supporting the transformation and upgrading of the economy, and fostering social harmony and stability. These centers are dedicated to cultivating skilled talents with socialist core values, contributing to the realization of the Chinese Dream of the great rejuvenation of the Chinese nation.
